The key point of the Jusung investigation is

97
00:06:02,268 --> 00:06:04,108
to prove the illegal activities conducted

98
00:06:04,108 --> 00:06:07,131
during the merger and acquisition at Jusung.

99
00:06:07,131 --> 00:06:10,048
First, Jusung's subsidiary, Jusung Chemical,

100
00:06:10,048 --> 00:06:13,547
changed the protocol for accounting management around the end of 2017,

101
00:06:13,547 --> 00:06:15,418
so they inflated the company's value.

102
00:06:15,418 --> 00:06:17,217
That's fraudulent accounting,

103
00:06:17,217 --> 00:06:19,818
so it violates the Capital Markets Act.

104
00:06:19,818 --> 00:06:21,528
While passing down the management rights

105
00:06:21,528 --> 00:06:22,988
and strengthening their authority,

106
00:06:22,988 --> 00:06:25,248
we must find out how many illegal—

107
00:06:33,297 --> 00:06:35,581
What do you think you're doing?

108
00:06:35,581 --> 00:06:38,307
We're in the middle of a meeting. If you need to talk to me,

109
00:06:38,307 --> 00:06:40,904
I'll go to your office, sir.

110
00:06:40,904 --> 00:06:45,547
So you do know that you report to me, right?

111
00:06:45,547 --> 00:06:47,924
Sit down. Sit down.

112
00:06:48,888 --> 00:06:51,079
I told you to sit down!

113
00:06:54,388 --> 00:06:57,897
I'll finish the meeting soon and be upstairs.

114
00:06:57,897 --> 00:06:59,657
So you remember that I'm your supervisor,

115
00:06:59,657 --> 00:07:02,398
but did you forget what I told you about this investigation?

116
00:07:02,398 --> 00:07:04,533
Don't finish the meeting soon.

117
00:07:04,533 --> 00:07:08,677
I want you to finish the meeting at this very minute. Stop it!

118
00:07:08,677 --> 00:07:11,328
I cannot do that.

119
00:07:15,348 --> 00:07:18,548
Are you going to defy orders from your supervisor?

120
00:07:18,548 --> 00:07:20,948
Article Seven of the Prosecutors' Office Act,

121
00:07:20,948 --> 00:07:22,718
"Regarding the affairs at prosecution,

122
00:07:22,718 --> 00:07:28,428
prosecutors must follow orders from their supervisors."

123
00:07:28,428 --> 00:07:31,340
That's the regulation we have.

124
00:07:31,340 --> 00:07:33,257
Are you his sidekick?

125
00:07:33,928 --> 00:07:35,428
What?

126
00:07:37,027 --> 00:07:39,398
The regulation in question was implemented to achieve unity

127
00:07:39,398 --> 00:07:41,738
when exercising rights as prosecutors. It's only a supplementary regulation.

128
00:07:41,738 --> 00:07:44,577
By setting up a nationally uniformed investigation network,

129
00:07:44,577 --> 00:07:46,557
we can be efficient.

130
00:07:46,557 --> 00:07:50,247
By balancing our rights to exercise our authority, we can maintain fairness.

131
00:07:50,247 --> 00:07:54,017
Also, it is established to control arbitrary decisions by prosecutors.

132
00:07:54,017 --> 00:07:57,747
Hence, Article Seven has nothing to do with the Jusung investigation,

133
00:07:57,747 --> 00:08:00,757
as it is clearly confirmed that they committed illegal activities,

134
00:08:00,757 --> 00:08:02,558
and that cannot be and will not be applied

135
00:08:02,558 --> 00:08:04,388
to prevent prosecutors from conducting

136
00:08:04,388 --> 00:08:06,698
investigations independently.

137
00:08:06,698 --> 00:08:08,698
If the regulation is used for that purpose,

138
00:08:08,698 --> 00:08:11,468
it will be an abuse of authority.

139
00:08:11,468 --> 00:08:15,371
It's considered a serious offense.

140
00:08:15,371 --> 00:08:19,111
What? A serious offense?

141
00:08:20,607 --> 00:08:23,247
Go ahead and do whatever you want.

142
00:08:41,398 --> 00:08:43,568
Just another day at the office, right?

143
00:08:43,568 --> 00:08:45,988
That's right.

144
00:08:45,988 --> 00:08:47,509
Let's sit down.

145
00:08:48,507 --> 00:08:52,024
All right. Where were we?

146
