147
00:09:19,898 --> 00:09:22,837
This year, we again came in second for the bar exam's pass rate.

148
00:09:22,837 --> 00:09:24,878
Two years in a row.

149
00:09:25,778 --> 00:09:27,808
I knew this would happen.

150
00:09:27,808 --> 00:09:29,307
What are we going to do now?

151
00:09:29,307 --> 00:09:32,518
It's imperative to secure our budget to recruit more professors

152
00:09:32,518 --> 00:09:34,177
and expand our scholarship program.

153
00:09:34,177 --> 00:09:37,247
How can we now ask for more funding after this?

154
00:09:37,247 --> 00:09:38,588
Don't you agree?

155
00:09:38,588 --> 00:09:41,157
The pass rate isn't everything.

156
00:09:41,157 --> 00:09:44,027
I'm sure you know that our graduates have

157
00:09:44,027 --> 00:09:46,257
stellar reputations at the courthouses,

158
00:09:46,257 --> 00:09:49,028
prosecutors' offices, and law firms.

159
00:09:49,028 --> 00:09:50,928
The pass rate isn't everything.

160
00:09:50,928 --> 00:09:52,597
"The pass rate isn't everything?"

161
00:09:52,597 --> 00:09:54,268
Then what are we doing here?

162
00:09:54,268 --> 00:09:55,737
What is this place?

163
00:09:55,737 --> 00:09:59,837
This is the law school where students learn about the law.

164
00:09:59,837 --> 00:10:01,237
The students here invest their precious time

165
00:10:01,237 --> 00:10:04,347
and work their heads off to pass the bar exam and practice law,

166
00:10:04,347 --> 00:10:06,148
and they spend a lot of money to learn from us.

167
00:10:06,148 --> 00:10:09,087
They must pass the bar exam to do anything as law officers!

168
00:10:09,087 --> 00:10:12,257
There is only the next step when they pass the exam!

169
00:10:12,257 --> 00:10:13,717
Ma'am,

170
00:10:13,717 --> 00:10:16,827
this is what Professor Na here thinks,

171
00:10:16,827 --> 00:10:20,158
so it doesn't matter how hard I try to help them pass the bar exam.

172
00:10:20,158 --> 00:10:23,698
- Don't you agree? 
 - This isn't some cram school.

173
00:10:23,698 --> 00:10:25,138
This is a graduate program.

174
00:10:25,138 --> 00:10:27,138
This isn't some prep school.

175
00:10:27,138 --> 00:10:30,568
Then, are you telling me I'm acting like an instructor at a prep school?

176
00:10:30,568 --> 00:10:33,207
Do you think I'm some businessman? I'm a professor too!

177
00:10:33,207 --> 00:10:36,077
My top priority is my students' needs!

178
00:10:36,077 --> 00:10:37,408
I'm an educator!

179
00:10:37,408 --> 00:10:39,717
As this is a graduate program at a law school,

180
00:10:39,717 --> 00:10:41,548
we ought to teach our students

181
00:10:41,548 --> 00:10:43,987
the academic side of the law, as well as the practicality of the law,

182
00:10:43,987 --> 00:10:46,717
so we shape them to be more than just people who practice law.

183
00:10:46,717 --> 00:10:49,029
I have a doctoral degree too!

184
00:10:51,597 --> 00:10:53,658
Ma'am, I apologize for my outburst.

185
00:10:53,658 --> 00:10:55,609
If this continues,

186
00:10:56,467 --> 00:10:58,237
I can't hold my lectures here.

187
00:10:58,237 --> 00:11:00,637
He's not even a tenured professor. He's just a showman.

188
00:11:00,637 --> 00:11:03,768
He's influencing our school with his mere image.

189
00:11:03,768 --> 00:11:06,548
I can no longer put up with this.

190
00:11:06,548 --> 00:11:08,007
I'm sorry.

191
00:11:11,048 --> 00:11:12,448
Professor Na,

192
00:11:12,448 --> 00:11:15,117
do whatever you want. Let's see what happens.

193
00:11:15,117 --> 00:11:16,388
Those kids from Seoul National University?

194
00:11:16,388 --> 00:11:18,658
They do nothing but study for exams,

195
00:11:18,658 --> 00:11:20,418
and the school is packed with kids

196
00:11:20,418 --> 00:11:22,227
whose parents are judges, prosecutors, and lawyers.

197
00:11:22,227 --> 00:11:24,487
That's a tight-knitted circle.

198
00:11:24,487 --> 00:11:26,658
Your pathetic principle of idealism

199
00:11:26,658 --> 00:11:29,826
is weakening the dominance of our school!

200
00:11:29,826 --> 00:11:32,398
What good is it when our students become judges or prosecutors?

201
00:11:32,398 --> 00:11:33,638
They won't be able to do a thing

202
00:11:33,638 --> 00:11:35,607
because those kids from SNU will outnumber them.

203
00:11:35,607 --> 00:11:38,278
So you'll take responsibility for that?

204
00:11:38,278 --> 00:11:41,798
When you're planning to quit teaching and become a politician?

205
00:11:42,678 --> 00:11:47,198
You know what? This is the only career I want for the rest of my life!

206
00:11:52,957 --> 00:11:55,313
Professor Hwang,

207
00:11:55,313 --> 00:11:57,756
I'm sure Professor Na

208
00:11:57,756 --> 00:12:00,597
understood the message behind your passionate speech,

209
00:12:00,597 --> 00:12:06,198
and I'm well-aware how hard you work for our school.

210
00:12:06,198 --> 00:12:08,186
I'm always grateful.

211
00:12:08,186 --> 00:12:09,408
Please excuse us.

212
00:12:09,408 --> 00:12:11,908
I still have a few things to say to Professor Na.

213
00:12:11,908 --> 00:12:15,678
Sure. I also have to work on the questions for the mock exams.

214
00:12:15,678 --> 00:12:17,481
I'll get going then.

215
00:12:22,347 --> 00:12:24,748
Reduce the number of your classes starting next semester.

216
00:12:24,748 --> 00:12:25,658
Pardon?

217
00:12:25,658 --> 00:12:29,087
Do you think this is a place for polishing your reputation?

218
00:12:29,087 --> 00:12:31,457
You're only misleading them, so stop holding lectures.

219
00:12:31,457 --> 00:12:34,666
- Mother— 
 - I'm not your mother.

220
00:12:34,666 --> 00:12:35,768
Your trick only works on Hye Ryul

221
00:12:35,768 --> 00:12:37,097
because she doesn't know any better,

222
00:12:37,097 --> 00:12:38,438
but to fall for your idealistic principles,

223
00:12:38,438 --> 00:12:40,878
how dare you think it would work on me?

224
00:12:40,878 --> 00:12:43,908
People are praising you because they fell for your act.

225
00:12:43,908 --> 00:12:45,908
Do you think you're an important professor?

226
00:12:45,908 --> 00:12:47,968
Do you think you can go higher?

227
00:12:47,968 --> 00:12:50,233
Know your place.

228
00:12:50,233 --> 00:12:51,740
Don't be arrogant.

229
00:12:53,347 --> 00:12:54,778
If we can't catch up with SNU's pass rate,

230
00:12:54,778 --> 00:12:57,329
I'll get rid of your lectures.

231
00:13:04,127 --> 00:13:06,198
- We need three people. 
 - Hey, this is nice.

232
00:13:06,198 --> 00:13:07,898
There are only two of us.

233
00:13:07,898 --> 00:13:09,768
- We're studying for this. 
 - Look at that.

234
00:13:09,768 --> 00:13:12,107
Do you want to join us? 
    

235
00:13:12,107 --> 00:13:14,837
- We just need one more person. 
 - Right. We just need one more person.

236
00:13:14,837 --> 00:13:16,568
We just need an extra person.

237
00:13:16,568 --> 00:13:18,007
- Let's ask one of our friends. 
 - Should we try it?

238
00:13:18,007 --> 00:13:20,837
- You must be in the same lecture. 
 - Let's go this way.

239
00:13:20,837 --> 00:13:22,778
All of my friends are preparing for it.

240
00:13:22,778 --> 00:13:24,308
I'm going to try out for the contest.

241
00:13:24,308 --> 00:13:27,418
You want to go for the contest on top of our study group and all?

242
00:13:27,418 --> 00:13:30,162
I don't have time for it.

243
00:13:30,162 --> 00:13:32,188
I don't think it's that necessary.

244
00:13:32,188 --> 00:13:33,918
It sounds fun, so I'll try it out.

245
00:13:33,918 --> 00:13:35,530
Same here.

246
00:13:35,530 --> 00:13:38,117
Then I'll join you too.

247
00:13:38,117 --> 00:13:40,197
You have to put aside at least two hours per day.

248
00:13:40,197 --> 00:13:41,158
You guys have time for that, right?

249
00:13:41,158 --> 00:13:43,198
On top of our study group and the bar exam lectures?

250
00:13:43,198 --> 00:13:44,568
You want us to put aside two more hours a day?

251
00:13:44,568 --> 00:13:47,698
A week before the contest, we'll do an all-nighter to prepare for it.

252
00:13:47,698 --> 00:13:50,458
Kang Baek, Kyung Yoon, are you guys up for it?

253
00:13:53,937 --> 00:13:54,948
What about you, Ji Yi?

254
00:13:54,948 --> 00:13:57,690
We can only have up to four people on our team for this contest.

255
00:14:02,048 --> 00:14:04,048
Why don't we do it together? I'll make more time for it.

256
00:14:04,048 --> 00:14:06,117
I just need you to do some research.

257
00:14:06,117 --> 00:14:08,457
Come to think of it, winning the award sounds pretty good.

258
00:14:08,457 --> 00:14:10,127
There's a benefit, and I can put it down on my resumé.

259
00:14:10,127 --> 00:14:12,798
That's if you win the award.

260
00:14:12,798 --> 00:14:15,028
I'll think about it.

261
00:14:15,028 --> 00:14:17,528
