00:30:40,178 --> 00:30:42,947
and takes what he thinks he deserves.

526
00:30:42,947 --> 00:30:44,748
Seeing him frustrates me to death,

527
00:30:44,748 --> 00:30:46,651
however...

528
00:30:46,651 --> 00:30:48,874
You're right, Father.

529
00:30:48,874 --> 00:30:50,928
Provoking him more won't do any good.

530
00:30:50,928 --> 00:30:53,728
I think a little differently.

531
00:30:53,728 --> 00:30:56,528
Grandpa, you're alive and well,

532
00:30:56,528 --> 00:30:58,828
but he leaves the way open and offers the main room.

533
00:30:58,828 --> 00:31:01,038
He will probably attempt to do more.

534
00:31:01,038 --> 00:31:04,608
At first, I was flustered that Ham &amp; Lee was under attack.

535
00:31:04,608 --> 00:31:06,408
Later, I doubted it.

536
00:31:06,408 --> 00:31:10,277
But the moment Won Kyung said his target was Na Geun Woo,

537
00:31:10,277 --> 00:31:12,913
I got a double take.

538
00:31:12,913 --> 00:31:16,247
I had forgotten the biggest problem

539
00:31:16,247 --> 00:31:18,587
was always within our family.

540
00:31:18,587 --> 00:31:21,757
Now that he has shown his claws, he might even go for the head.

541
00:31:21,757 --> 00:31:27,128
He intends to take over Ham &amp; Lee regardless of your presence.

542
00:31:27,128 --> 00:31:29,004
I won't let that happen!

543
00:31:29,004 --> 00:31:31,267
I will get his head instead.

544
00:31:31,267 --> 00:31:35,197
Grandpa, a conflict will cause damage in any way,

545
00:31:35,197 --> 00:31:39,778
and people are waiting for that to happen around me.

546
00:31:39,778 --> 00:31:42,307
I can't give them what they want.

547
00:31:42,307 --> 00:31:44,148
But he is obviously determined.

548
00:31:44,148 --> 00:31:46,848
Will there be a way to avoid conflict?

549
00:31:48,418 --> 00:31:51,213
I will cut off his connections.

550
00:31:51,213 --> 00:31:52,570
Connections?

551
00:31:52,570 --> 00:31:54,060
Yes.

552
00:31:54,065 --> 00:31:56,897
Those who chime and instigate him,

553
00:31:56,897 --> 00:32:00,198
I will cut them off from him and bring them to my side.

554
00:32:00,198 --> 00:32:03,098
That's the only way to bind his hand and foot.

555
00:32:03,098 --> 00:32:07,201
I will embrace his surroundings.

556
00:32:09,168 --> 00:32:10,707
I've known her since she was little.

557
00:32:10,707 --> 00:32:12,737
She is easygoing and kind.

558
00:32:12,737 --> 00:32:15,537
I don't mind having her as my daughter-in-law.

559
00:32:15,537 --> 00:32:19,689
I will embrace Ji Yi.

560
00:32:20,247 --> 00:32:24,328
The daughter of the head of the Central District Office...

561
00:32:24,328 --> 00:32:28,517
That will only complicate the situation.

562
00:32:29,987 --> 00:32:32,128
Won't it shrink your world?

563
00:32:32,128 --> 00:32:35,188
The one who loves more is always on the losing end.

564
00:32:35,188 --> 00:32:38,954
Ji Yi likes Kang Baek a lot,

565
00:32:38,954 --> 00:32:43,255
and with her as a hostage, I won't have to walk on eggshells.

566
00:32:44,207 --> 00:32:47,438
Kang Baek, just why are you being like this?

567
00:32:47,438 --> 00:32:48,778
What is it this time?

568
00:32:48,778 --> 00:32:50,533
"This time?"

569
00:32:50,533 --> 00:32:52,708
I'm not a wife who grills her husband.

570
00:32:52,708 --> 00:32:54,247
Don't put it like that.

571
00:32:54,247 --> 00:32:56,888
What is it that annoyed you this time?

572
00:32:56,888 --> 00:33:00,228
Everything. Everything annoys me.

573
00:33:00,228 --> 00:33:01,918
I just don't understand how you behave around Hong Nan Hee.

574
00:33:01,918 --> 00:33:04,287
- You're always at her beck. 
 - I'm not.

575
00:33:04,287 --> 00:33:06,358
You are. Do you even know what others say?

576
00:33:06,358 --> 00:33:08,398
What others say doesn't matter.

577
00:33:08,398 --> 00:33:10,698
I get along with her because she's a close friend.

578
00:33:10,698 --> 00:33:13,558
All right, she's a close friend of yours.

579
00:33:13,558 --> 00:33:16,029
What about me then?

580
00:33:16,029 --> 00:33:19,038
You decided on the competition without asking me in advance.

581
00:33:19,038 --> 00:33:20,310
I apologized for that.

582
00:33:20,310 --> 00:33:22,410
Just that?

583
00:33:22,417 --> 00:33:25,078
Is that all you thought you should apologize for?

584
00:33:25,078 --> 00:33:27,377
How could you treat me like this?

585
00:33:27,377 --> 00:33:29,118
Think of how you behave these days.

586
00:33:29,118 --> 00:33:31,687
What do I mean to you?

587
00:33:31,687 --> 00:33:34,467
A pretty and cute friend.

588
00:33:35,257 --> 00:33:36,942
And?

589
00:33:38,127 --> 00:33:39,228
- Ji Yi. 
 - And?

590
00:33:39,228 --> 00:33:42,063
Other than a friend!

591
00:33:42,063 --> 00:33:43,820
Ji Yi, you see—

592
00:33:43,820 --> 00:33:46,470
Try harder!

593
00:33:47,521 --> 00:33:50,905
I've known you since kindergarten.

594
00:33:50,905 --> 00:33:53,696
You always had my heart.

595
00:33:54,408 --> 00:33:59,417
You comforted me, appeased me, and supported me.

596
00:33:59,417 --> 00:34:03,500
I can't imagine my life without you.

597
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:07,288
- Ji Yi, that's— 
 - If you were going to break my heart now,

598
00:34:07,288 --> 00:34:10,408
you shouldn't have been so kind from the start.

599
00:34:11,757 --> 00:34:14,201
So try harder.

600
00:34:18,498 --> 00:34:21,738
If all this is because of Hong Nan Hee,

601
00:34:24,537 --> 00:34:26,858
I will never forgive you.

602
00:34:35,877 --> 00:34:37,482
I'm sorry.

603
00:35:13,187 --> 00:35:15,058
I don't feel like having Korean food today.

604
00:35:15,058 --> 00:35:17,598
Would you like to have Western food instead?

605
00:35:19,058 --> 00:35:22,158
You're offering to change the menu right away. That's not fun.

606
00:35:22,158 --> 00:35:25,367
If I say, "It's going to take a lot of time,

607
00:35:25,367 --> 00:35:27,967
so please have what was served today,"

608
00:35:27,967 --> 00:35:30,868
you can throw another fit and say,

609
00:35:30,868 --> 00:35:33,407
"Are you telling me to stop complaining and just eat?"

610
00:35:33,407 --> 00:35:34,890
Will it be fun for you then?

611
00:35:34,890 --> 00:35:36,180
Do you take joke lessons?

612
00:35:36,180 --> 00:35:38,478
You can't learn how to make jokes.

613
00:35:38,478 --> 00:35:43,620
If you think I have a sense of humor, I must be a natural.

614
00:35:44,687 --> 00:35:48,091
That was hilarious!

615
00:35:48,091 --> 00:35:51,618
Your sense of humor calls for violence.

616
00:35:51,618 --> 00:35:53,342
What?

617
00:35:53,342 --> 00:35:56,627
Why don't you again talk back at me with your gifted sense of humor?

618
00:35:56,627 --> 00:35:59,598
Now you come at me every time I speak.

619
00:35:59,598 --> 00:36:02,822
Am I a joke to you?

620
00:36:02,822 --> 00:36:05,302
Answer me!

621
00:36:06,277 --> 00:36:08,534
That crazy witch is at it again.

622
00:36:08,534 --> 00:36:10,647
She's a total lunatic.

623
00:36:10,647 --> 00:36:13,518
Geez, I might be asked to set the table again.

624
00:36:13,518 --> 00:36:16,147
I can't believe they took someone like her into this family.

625
00:36:16,147 --> 00:36:17,387
They probably didn't know.

626
00:36:17,387 --> 00:36:18,948
They wouldn't have done it had they known.

627
00:36:18,948 --> 00:36:22,087
She becomes a refined lady around the family.

628
00:36:22,087 --> 00:36:23,928
Doesn't Ms. Yang tell them about her?

629
00:36:23,928 --> 00:36:26,297
Come on, I bet the family knows.

630
00:36:26,297 --> 00:36:28,357
There's no way they are unaware of her temper.

631
00:36:28,357 --> 00:36:31,502
They must be just feigning ignorance.

632
00:36:31,502 --> 00:36:35,937
I always say this, but whatever they have in mind,

633
00:36:35,937 --> 00:36:39,497
this family lives a life full of trouble.

634
00:36:39,497 --> 00:36:40,607
All right.

635
00:36:40,607 --> 00:36:42,337
Since she knocked over the Korean meal,

636
00:36:42,337 --> 00:36:44,078
let's try the Western meal this time.

637
00:36:44,078 --> 00:36:47,478
I'm going to make steak, a salad, and consommé.

638
00:36:47,478 --> 00:36:49,217
Get me the broth.

639
00:36:49,217 --> 00:36:50,647
Gosh.

640
00:36:50,647 --> 00:36:53,618
The dishes she smashed today are worth more than my monthly pay

641
00:36:53,618 --> 00:36:55,217
and she did it without even batting an eye!

642
00:36:55,217 --> 00:36:58,058
That lunatic's madness is ruining my mood!

643
00:36:58,058 --> 00:37:01,260
- Darn her! 
 - Drop this madness!

644
00:37:04,067 --> 00:37:06,740
Hey!

645
00:37:14,138 --> 00:37:16,697
Hey!

646
00:37:19,408 --> 00:37:21,478
Hey!

647
00:37:21,478 --> 00:37:25,150
- Let go of me! 
 - Don't move.

648
00:37:25,150 --> 00:37:27,437
What do you think you are doing?

649
00:37:29,388 --> 00:37:32,675
You darn scums!

650
00:37:34,498 --> 00:37:37,728
A get-together must be with nothing more expensive than ox bone soup,

651
00:37:37,728 --> 00:37:42,237
but this seems pricey enough for me to worry about future trouble.

652
00:37:42,237 --> 00:37:44,422
This is why

653
00:37:44,422 --> 00:37:46,908
I admire judicial officers,

654
00:37:46,908 --> 00:37:49,168
because they know the law,

655
00:37:49,168 --> 00:37:53,293
they're careful and cautious at all times.

656
00:37:53,293 --> 00:37:56,448
Are you saying we're cowards?

657
00:37:56,448 --> 00:37:59,495
That's right.

658
00:38:00,888 --> 00:38:02,288
If you know the law,

659
00:38:02,288 --> 00:38:07,328
you must be scared of how frightening the law can be.

660
00:38:07,328 --> 00:38:09,257
It's not about just one person.

661
00:38:09,257 --> 00:38:12,725
Three generations of a family can be ruined in an instant.

662
00:38:16,797 --> 00:38:20,208
There you go suspecting again.

663
00:38:20,208 --> 00:38:23,607
There's nothing here.

664
00:38:23,607 --> 00:38:27,100
Recorders and cameras? There's nothing like them here.

665
00:38:27,147 --> 00:38:28,817
Should I show you?

666
00:38:28,817 --> 00:38:31,487
Goodness, you don't believe me.

667
00:38:31,487 --> 00:38:33,217
- I have nothing. 
 - Gosh!

668
00:38:33,217 --> 00:38:36,602
Please stop and sit down.

669
00:38:36,602 --> 00:38:38,887
- I have absolutely nothing! 
 - I see.

670
00:38:38,887 --> 00:38:41,328
- Let's talk at ease. 
 - Gosh.

671
00:38:41,328 --> 00:38:42,763
Sure.

672
00:38:42,763 --> 00:38:45,515
Goodness.

673
00:38:47,268 --> 00:38:49,737
You're the butler of Ham &amp; Lee law corporation.

674
00:38:49,737 --> 00:38:53,978
According to Mr. Ham, your job is to clean up the mess.

675
00:38:53,978 --> 00:38:56,670
Isn't that right, Mr. Nam?

676
00:38:58,248 --> 00:39:02,388
Don't be upset.

677
00:39:02,388 --> 00:39:05,188
Mr. Ham says that about Na Geun Woo too,

678
00:39:05,188 --> 00:39:07,943
that he used to clean up his mess,

679
00:39:07,943 --> 00:39:14,098
but these days, he thinks he got stabbed in the back.

680
00:39:14,098 --> 00:39:20,337
His former underling seduced his daughter into joining his family,

681
00:39:20,337 --> 00:39:22,693
and now, he's after Ham &amp; Lee.

682
00:39:23,208 --> 00:39:29,308
So, are you saying you can't and won't trust me?

683
00:39:29,308 --> 00:39:31,748
You talk just like him!

684
00:39:31,748 --> 00:39:34,348
He said exactly the same thing.

685
00:39:34,348 --> 00:39:38,317
You're different indeed, Mr. Nam.

686
00:39:38,317 --> 00:39:41,357
This is why Mr. Ham of Ham &amp; Lee law corporation

687
00:39:41,357 --> 00:39:46,694
keeps you very close to him, even when he can't trust you.

688
00:39:48,127 --> 00:39:49,783
You see,

689
00:39:49,783 --> 00:39:52,297
I thought I could break through this crisis

690
00:39:52,297 --> 00:39:54,837
only with his help in any way.

691
00:39:54,837 --> 00:40:00,062
So I begged him with every means, except for going down on my knees,

692
00:40:00,062 --> 00:40:02,505
but you know what he's like.

693
00:40:02,505 --> 00:40:05,808
He's willing to take me down at any time.

694
00:40:05,808 --> 00:40:07,147
Isn't this too harsh?

695
00:40:07,147 --> 00:40:11,447
Honestly speaking, I had what could put Ham &amp; Lee into trouble.

696
00:40:11,447 --> 00:40:16,157
We agreed to join hands, so I thought we'd be partners no matter what.

697
00:40:16,157 --> 00:40:18,527
Goodness. Let me keep this short.

698
00:40:18,527 --> 00:40:24,112
I'd like to ask you for your help.

699
00:40:25,967 --> 00:40:29,743
Do you have a mess to be cleaned?

700
00:40:31,737 --> 00:40:34,608
A lawyer's job is to clean up a mess.

701
00:40:34,608 --> 00:40:37,078
A mess is the same, whoever causes it.

702
00:40:37,078 --> 00:40:39,107
There's not much of a difference in how dirty and smelly it is.

703
00:40:39,107 --> 00:40:42,492
I'm not so picky at choosing what to clean up.

704
00:40:44,417 --> 00:40:46,101
So,

705
00:40:46,101 --> 00:40:49,927
you don't mind whoever and whatever mess you clean up?

706
00:40:49,927 --> 00:40:51,360
You will clean it up?

707
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:52,980
That won't be all.

708
00:40:52,987 --> 00:40:57,816
As long as it's worthy, I can swallow it and even take the blame.

709
00:40:59,527 --> 00:41:01,316
Goodness.

710
00:41:01,316 --> 00:41:04,538
Only if I get to have someone like you on my side,

711
00:41:04,538 --> 00:41:08,854
I'll be at ease regardless of how much trouble I cause.

712
00:41:11,047 --> 00:41:14,147
Anyway, I'm sorry for not even touching the food,

713
00:41:14,147 --> 00:41:16,348
but I will make up for this

714
00:41:16,348 --> 00:41:19,388
with the determination to swallow and take the blame,

715
00:41:19,388 --> 00:41:20,888
when I get the chance to clean something up.

716
00:41:20,888 --> 00:41:24,847
I like to keep things clear.

717
00:41:24,847 --> 00:41:27,660
Whether it's my mess or Mr. Ham's,

718
00:41:27,660 --> 00:41:30,741
you don't care at all. Is that it?

719
00:41:30,741 --> 00:41:33,248
Anyone can become a lawyer these days.

720
00:41:33,248 --> 00:41:36,640
When you're paid to do the job, you don't care whose mess it is.

721
00:41:38,808 --> 00:41:41,903
Well... I'll be off, then.

722
00:42:13,607 --> 00:42:17,716
Close the door, will you? I can smell the filthy mess.

723
00:42:20,348 --> 00:42:22,417
   

724
00:42:22,417 --> 00:42:23,977
   

725
00:42:25,917 --> 00:42:28,058
- Yes, sir. 
 - Hey, how did it go?

726
00:42:28,058 --> 00:42:30,393
I just left.

727
00:42:31,458 --> 00:42:35,902
He kept talking about cleaning up messes when we met for dinner.

728
00:42:35,902 --> 00:42:38,198
He's about to wet his pants because he's scared,

729
00:42:38,198 --> 00:42:43,198
thinking he's made a big mess, yet he's still bluffing.

730
00:42:43,198 --> 00:42:48,230
I have to say, I think he'll be the easiest one to maneuver.

731
00:42:48,230 --> 00:42:52,901
Right, I see. Sounds like he has an unusual taste.

732
00:42:52,901 --> 00:42:57,032
Does talking about filth stimulate his appetite or something?

733
00:42:59,018 --> 00:43:01,757
Did he talk about anything else?

734
00:43:01,757 --> 00:43:04,677
That's all he talked about the whole time?

735
00:43:06,958 --> 00:43:08,558
Okay, let's think about that.

736
00:43:08,558 --> 00:43:11,330
I always trust your judgment, you know.

737
00:43:11,330 --> 00:43:14,737
So you think Mr. Ahn is the easiest one to maneuver.

738
00:43:14,737 --> 00:43:19,237
Those who wet their pants and bluff are always the biggest pushovers.

739
00:43:20,007 --> 00:43:21,478
You should call it an early night.

740
00:43:21,478 --> 00:43:24,560
You must be exhausted after listening to his pathetic spiel.

741
00:43:27,917 --> 00:43:29,948
Oh, have some food.

742
00:43:29,948 --> 00:43:32,888
I bet you were too busy talking about your messes to eat earlier.

743
00:43:32,888 --> 00:43:34,623
Go on and eat.

744
00:43:34,623 --> 00:43:37,647
Don't sit there grimacing.

745
00:43:42,498 --> 00:43:45,728
I shouldn't have come today.

746
00:43:45,728 --> 00:43:47,737
That's not true. You should be here.

747
00:43:47,737 --> 00:43:50,607
Director Yoon, this is how you learn.

748
00:43:50,607 --> 00:43:52,268
This is how things work in politics.

749
00:43:52,268 --> 00:43:54,978
Swallow and spit.

750
00:43:54,978 --> 00:43:56,877
You have to master that craft.

751
00:43:56,877 --> 00:43:58,448
If it's sweet, don't swallow it,

752
00:43:58,448 --> 00:44:00,968
and don't spit it out even if it's bitter.

753
00:44:01,848 --> 00:44:06,176
It can save you or get you fired.

754
00:44:07,357 --> 00:44:10,753
I'm learning a lot from you.

755
00:44:11,388 --> 00:44:13,336
Please, let's eat.

756
00:44:28,277 --> 00:44:30,873
I saw the interview.

757
00:44:30,873 --> 00:44:36,478
Professor Hwang, I did not know that you were thinking that.

758
00:44:36,478 --> 00:44:39,661
Ma'am, the thing is...

759
00:44:39,661 --> 00:44:43,857
To be honest, considering the recent incidents

760
00:44:43,857 --> 00:44:47,598
involving Jusung, we can't say that there are no problems...

761
00:44:47,598 --> 00:44:49,728
Those who enjoy all the privileges

762
00:44:49,728 --> 00:44:51,527
come with their professor titles,

763
00:44:51,527 --> 00:44:53,268
including their six-figure salaries,

764
00:44:53,268 --> 00:44:56,938
while vying for the opportunity to kick-start their political careers.

765
00:44:56,938 --> 00:44:59,538
You used to despise such professors. Am I wrong?

766
00:44:59,538 --> 00:45:02,125
I'm sorry.

767
00:45:02,125 --> 00:45:04,942
They got in touch with me urgently,

768
00:45:04,942 --> 00:45:08,748
- so I couldn't turn it down. 
 - I see.

769
00:45:08,748 --> 00:45:10,968
- Was it Jang Il? 
 - Pardon me?

770
00:45:10,968 --> 00:45:13,767
Did he ask you to do it?

771
00:45:13,767 --> 00:45:18,858
- Ma'am, it was... 
 - Ji Yi

772
00:45:18,858 --> 00:45:22,398
gets good grades in the class that you teach.

773
00:45:22,398 --> 00:45:24,467
She always gets an A plus.

774
00:45:24,467 --> 00:45:28,248
In her other classes, she gets mediocre grades.

775
00:45:37,408 --> 00:45:40,148
You should reflect on yourself first,

776
00:45:40,148 --> 00:45:43,348
before you run your mouth about others' family matters.

777
00:45:47,288 --> 00:45:52,336
Yes. You're right, ma'am.

778
00:45:57,127 --> 00:45:59,335
   

